						<summary>

						<p>On the south wall, central shrine, Anantēśvarasvāmin temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 10: 981 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records a gift of 20 <hi rend="italic">īḻakkāśu</hi> which was deposited with the <hi rend="italic">Saṅkarappāḍiyār</hi> of Tugaḍi in Vīranārāyaṇa-chaturvēdimaṅgalam for the daily supply of an <hi rend="italic">uḻakku</hi> of oil for burning a perpetual lamp in the temple of Tiruvanantīśvarattu-paramasvāmi of the above village by Sembiyaṉ Mūvēndavēḷāṉ of Maruttu Paṉaippākkam in Muṉaippāḍi. He also donated an ornamental lamp for that purpose.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. XIX No. 263. </p>						

						</summary>
